It seems that there are one or more cyber trolls who have, from time to time, spiced up life by posting under a variety of names, anaon's, etc., just to cause trouble. They probably cause trouble elsewhere, too. <br><br>
Vietnam Veterans can handle just about anything. I think we all have amply demonstrated that at one time or another when someone comes on line who is hurting real bad and is looking for help, or a crackpot decides to push our buttons, and we completely eradicate its effectiveness.<br><br>
To the credit of all the decent folks on this site, Vietnam Veterans and interested just plain folks, I feel we have evolved to the point where we can just start really ignoring these individuals who cause trouble and whose only satisfaction in life seems to be to inflict pain on others by remote control. We owe it to ourselves, and everyone else, to do this.<br><br>
I feel what we need to do is to ignore everything that is obscene, infalmmatory, baiting, and truly anonomous, leapfrog over the stuff, and let POV worry about sweeping it up and tossing it in the garbage. That *includes* posts by Barry Spatz, alleged, real, or otherwise.<br><br>
Many of us talk to one another by telephone. The cyber trolls can't invade that, and we need to keep open alternative lines of communication between our selves to keep our sanity here.<br><br>
There is a lot of work left to do here. There are many people who have yet to post who have an honest interest or need to heal.<br><br>
Let's help the good stuff along!   
